====Derived terms====
*[[പള്ളീലച്ഛന്]]..........Christian priest.
*[[വല്ല്യച്ഛന്]]..........Older paternal uncle. Literally "big father".
*[[കൊച്ചച്ഛന്]]..........Younger paternal uncle. Literally "small father".
====Synonyms====

*[[പിതാവ്]]..........This word was derived from Sanskrit ''pitr'' and is considered very formal.
*[[തന്ത]]..........This is a very colloquial and rude term meaning father.
*[[ബാപ്പ]]..........This is the word that most Muslims who speak malayalam use for father.
*[[അപ്പന്]]''or'' [[അപ്പച്ചന്]].......... These are usually used by Christians who use അച്ഛന് to refer to priests (with irregular vocative അച്ഛോ most of the time).

